    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with **Pete Crow-Armstrong** serving as our clear offensive anchor. With an elite efficiency score of 75.89, he benefits from a favorable matchup against Nelson, R, and a significant 14% boost from his dynamic platoon advantage. **Colt Keith** (65.83) and **Junior Caminero** (64.04) follow closely as our most reliable high-floor plays. **Colt Keith** is particularly well-positioned given the 6% boost from his #3 spot in the order, while **Junior Caminero** remains a locked-in starter despite a slight park penalty, as his raw power and platoon edge against Roupp provide the production ceiling we require.\n\nWe are prioritizing stolen base potential today, which explains why **Caleb Durbin** earns a starting nod despite his #9 spot in the lineup. His massive 19% SP skill advantage and the 2% bump from facing a slow delivery suggests he is primed to exploit the basepaths, even if his batting order limits his RBI potential. Our most difficult bench decision involved **Chase Meidroth** (44.21). While he offered a decent baseline, he was ultimately sidelined because his projected efficiency\u2014dampened by a negative park factor and an unfavorable platoon split\u2014simply could not surpass the higher-upside profiles of our deep middle-infield options. \n\nThe lineup faces two primary points of friction: **Yordan Alvarez** and **Trea Turner**. **Yordan Alvarez** is being started despite a difficult matchup against Early (L) because his elite xwOBA (0.434) outweighs the 19% SP skill penalty and 9% platoon deficit. Conversely, **Trea Turner** must navigate a tough contest against Meyer, though his high-leadoff position keeps him safely in the \"Strong\" category. Monitor weather and late lineup changes, as the high-stakes nature of our bench depth means we have zero margin for error if any of these starters are scratched late.",
